@startuml
title User Class - School Management System

hide circle
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam ClassBorderColor #334155
skinparam ClassBackgroundColor white
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FEF9C3
skinparam NoteBorderColor #A16207

class User {
    -id: bigint
    -name: string
    -email: string
    -phone: string
    -preferred_language: string
    -bio: text
    -requested_role: string
    -date_of_birth: date
    -parent_id: bigint
    -requested_course_id: bigint
    -approved_at: datetime
    -rejected_at: datetime
    -rejection_reason: text
    -approved_by: bigint
    -email_verified_at: datetime
    -password_changed_at: datetime

    +enrolledClasses()
    +taughtClasses()
    +parent()
    +children()
    +requestedCourse()
    +attendanceRecords()
    +latestStudentCard()
    +currentStudentCard()
    +studentTuition()
    +employeePayment()
    +getStudentAgeAttribute(): int
}

note right of User
Student, Teacher, Secretary, Parent,
and Admin are roles of the User model.

The User entity stores common account data,
approval information, parent-child links,
and course registration requests.

Role-specific behavior is handled through
permissions, controllers, middleware,
and services.
end note

@enduml